                        <interp inst="t18540130-name-152" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED BUTLER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police sergeant, F</hi> 36). I took the prisoner into custody at a public house in Long Acre on 19th Jan., for uttering a bad shilling—he gave his name, William Cleaver, No. 26, Gough-street, Gray's-inn-road—I went there—it is his father and mother's house.</p>
